.TH "HASHER" "1" "May 2026" "ccc" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
hasher-hash - Hash a password


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBhasher hash [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Hash reads a password and prints its hashed form.

.PP
The password is taken from --password if set, otherwise from a piped stdin,
otherwise from a hidden TTY prompt (confirmed by default).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for hash

.PP
\fB--no-confirm\fP[=false]
	skip the confirmation prompt at TTY

.PP
\fB-p\fP, \fB--password\fP=""
	password (insecure: visible in shell history)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--algo\fP="argon2"
	hash algorithm: bcrypt or argon2

.PP
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default: $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/hasher/hasher.yaml)

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	output format: text or json


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Interactive prompt (recommended)
  hasher hash

  # Pipe from stdin
  printf '%s' 'hunter2' | hasher hash --algo bcrypt

  # JSON output
  hasher hash --output json <<< 'hunter2'
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBhasher(1)\fP


